steps.branch:
per-item sub-flow:
  1. multi-choice → stock status {in stock, out of stock, not sold at this store}
  2. if in stock:
     a. photo → single frame showing item AND its shelf price tag together
     b. short-text → literal shelf-tag price (numeric, $ prefix)
     c. short-text → package size or weight as printed (numeric)
     d. multi-choice → unit {oz, lb, gal, dozen, count/each, ml, L}
     e. (produce only) multi-choice → priced as {per pound, per single unit / each}
  3. if out of stock: capture only (no photo, no price)
  4. if not sold at this store: capture only

per-item sub-flow (mirrors the in-store flow):
  1. multi-choice → availability {found, out-of-stock, not-sold-online, couldn't-find-after-reasonable-search}
  2. if found:
     a. screenshot → product listing page showing the item AND its listed price together
     b. short-text → literal listed price (numeric, $ prefix)
     c. short-text → package size as displayed on the listing
     d. multi-choice → unit {oz, lb, gal, dozen, count, ml, L}
     e. (produce only) multi-choice → priced as {per pound, per single unit}
  3. if not-found / not-sold / couldn't-find: capture only (no screenshot, no price) — this is a valid finding
